BM   hmmbuild  -o /dev/null HMM SEED
SM   hmmsearch --cpu 8 -Z 90746521 -E 1000 HMM pfamseq
TP   Domain
CC   This entry represents an N-terminal domain (approximately 140-170
CC   residues, positions 27-279) found in lytic transglycosylase
CC   proteins. This domain precedes the catalytic SLT domain
CC   (Pfam:PF01464). Lytic transglycosylases cleave the beta-1,4-glycosidic
CC   bond between N-acetylmuramic acid and N-acetylglucosamine in
CC   peptidoglycan, playing important roles in cell wall remodelling and
CC   recycling. The family is found in Alphaproteobacteria, particularly
CC   in Rhodospirillales, Caulobacterales (Caulobacteraceae), and
CC   Acetobacterales (Roseomonadaceae).
